##Quarantine personnel at home as soon as they open the door! Six out of 10 people support 'smart seal' trial

Micro Signal Ai

What features and rules do we expect to establish before the singularity Ethics of artificial intelligence? Welcome to AI SPACE FOR DISCUSSION!

With the increasing number of reworkers, community prevention and control has become a top priority. Ai Outposts have noticed that communities in Suzhou, Shanghai, Hangzhou and elsewhere are using "smart seals" to prevent people from leaving their homes without permission. It is understood that "smart seal" using the Internet of things, 5G and other technologies, can monitor the opening and closing state of the door, once the abnormal opening of the door, the community staff's mobile phones, computer terminals will be alerted.

Smart Seals for precision management in multi-site communities

"room XXX, unit X, building XX, Xiantang Street, Suzhou Park, Jiangsu Province

On February 19, you Xiantang street grid worker in Suzhou Industrial Park received this alert from the "smart seal" .

You Xiulan is in charge of 10 residential buildings in Lianhua district, Xiantang Street. She has been working overtime since the Spring Festival. Previously, the community to home quarantine personnel affixed to paper seals, she would go to the door every morning and evening to check. Once she's got the smart seal, she just needs to pay attention to her phone.

It is understood that the "smart seal" used in Xiantang street is actually a kind of door magnetic monitoring product, which is based on the Internet of things and can monitor the switch status of the door. The background system input the phone number of home quarantine personnel, quarantine period and other information, once the door magnetic monitoring to abnormal open the door, community personnel can receive notice.

"This is actually more convenient. If there is a police call at night and I can't get there, I can also quickly notify the residential property and let them go to the house, " you Xiulan said, smart Seals did relieve her stress at work, and the residents were cooperative. Despite the occasional mistouch of a resident, she received almost no warning from the seal.

Xiantang street told AI outpost, Xiantang street there are a large number of workers returning to the Soviet Union, but the streets, community staff limited, unable to focus on the 24-hour home supervision of Lisu personnel. As a result, the streets have experimented with smart seals, and about 100 have been installed since February 5.

Home Quarantine personnel can not go out, to buy food, take out the trash how to do? You said the streets have set up wechat groups for home quarantine workers, along with grid workers and volunteers to provide services. Quarantine personnel what needs to be put forward in the wechat group, by you Xiulan and colleagues to help.

Ai Outpost combing found that not only Suzhou, but also communities in Shanghai, Zhengzhou, Hangzhou, Jinhua, Wuxi and other cities across the country are experimenting with Smart Seals, more than 1,300 sets of equipment have been installed in the streets of Zhongshan, Songjiang District, Shanghai. These devices work in much the same way, and are favored by the community primarily because they are unplugged, have no wireless connection, can be reused, and warn in a timely manner.

60% of voters support smart seals in the community

Since the outbreak of NCP, many new technologies, such as big data and artificial intelligence, have been applied in the prevention and control of NCP. What do netizens think about the use of smart seals in the community? Ai Outposts have launched a campaign to vote on the issue at "hot spots" in Nandu. As of the afternoon of February 20, a total of 2,415 netizens had participated in the voting, of which 1,568 were "for" and 847 were "against" . In other words, 64.9% of voters supported the community approach.

Ai Outposts have noted that the use of seals has become a common practice in communities to manage home quarantine following outbreaks. Many communities don't use smart seals, but they do use plain paper seals. 56.7% of the voters believe that the seal can effectively play a role in prevention and control. However, 28.4% of netizens believe that the seal has a certain role but not necessary, belongs to "excessive prevention and control. ".

In a further survey, 49.3 percent of netizens thought the smart seal was better than the ordinary paper seal, and 6 percent thought the two kinds of seals were similar. Another 38.8 percent of netizens chose not to support the use of seals.

There is no denying that the seal, home isolation personnel will lose part of the freedom of movement and privacy. Whether should let the home segregates the personnel to make the right transfer? Opinions Differ Online.

58.2% of netizens believe that the epidemic situation is serious, quarantine personnel should and is necessary to make part of the sacrifice. "The interests of the majority are greater than the interests of a very small number of people. " "extraordinary measures can only be taken in extraordinary times. " "using high-tech prevention to improve the effectiveness of control. " Netizens "Gui" "Xiao Yi Hong" "grassland horses" left the above views.

38.8 percent of Internet users said they should not, as long as the quarantine personnel wear masks, wash their hands frequently and other scientific prevention and control can. Netizen"Cloud Sea"think, can advocate can supervise, but can not force, the basic right of dweller wants safeguard. "If you say you can trust the country, you should trust the people, " he said.

Residents'informed consent must be obtained and technology abuse must be prevented, scholars warn

Behind the different views of netizens, there are actually ethical issues related to the application of new technologies. Around this issue, Ai outpost consulted two ethics scholars.

"The use of technology to replace dangerous, boring, heavy work reflects the ethical intent of technology for human well-being. At the same time, the development of technology makes us reflect on the ethical status of human beings, the ethical attributes of technology, the ethical functions of technology in different situations, and so on,"said Yan Hongxiu, a professor at Shanghai Jiao Tong University, intelligent seal is a kind of special scene ethics case used in epidemic prevention and control. For such a special situation, it needs to be analyzed on the basis of general ethics in combination with specific circumstances.

She points out that the ethical motive for using smart seals in places such as Suzhou is well intentioned: to warn people to quarantine their homes and prevent the spread of the disease. At the same time, the data collected by the seal is limited, and remote data acquisition can reduce the cross-infection, reduce the human cost and improve the efficiency of management and governance.

"from the perspective of Public Safety and governance, it is lawful and necessary to take all technical means to ensure public safety in accordance with the law, " said Yang Qingfeng, a professor at Fudan University, intelligent seal can effectively control the population dynamics from the key epidemic areas, in this special period there is a certain legitimacy and necessity. Technologies such as Internet of things, big data and artificial intelligence, represented by intelligent seals, are used in epidemic prevention and control, that is, to ensure the safety of other people (such as community managers, residents of the same building) through unmanned and automated means, and also in line with the principles of bioethics to protect the lives of others.

While affirming the role of intelligent seals, Yan Hongxiu and Yang Qingfeng also put forward some suggestions from the perspective of technical ethics.

"giving the function of collecting data to the smart seal does not transfer the responsibility to technology, but only highlights the human's sense of responsibility. " Yan said the use of the smart seal should be based on residents' informed consent, only the data necessary for epidemic prevention and control can be collected, and technical authority can not be abused. Secondly, the data collected by the community can only be used for epidemic prevention and control, can not be placed in other scenarios, and can not be re-mined for other purposes.

Yang Qingfeng believes that the current application scenario of smart seals is unique, and it is necessary to study the ethical issues of post-disaster related technologies in other scenarios. For example, how do you distinguish between people who are sensitive and those who are most at risk? How to establish the ethical choice standard of the relevant scene? In addition, the effects of the use of smart seals in special periods also need to be studied. "residents who have been fitted with smart seals are being given special attention as if they are being given a special label, and the psychological state of these people being managed by technology needs further study, " he said.
